_:d2d0cbdb9ba589604663ddc6e2779712 a <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E52_Time-span> ;
	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "He was a saintly figure from Goǧǧām, a contemporary of ʾaṣe \n                  Yoḥannǝs I and  ʾaṣe\n                  ʾIyāsu I. Towards the end of his life, Zarʾa Buruk appears to have been involved in the \n                  Christological controversies of his time. As a result of his disagreeing with ʾaṣe \n                  ʾIyāsu I,  he was imprisoned for five years. \n                  His centre  of veneration is the church dedicated to him, St Michael at Gǝš ʾAbbāy. \n    " .
